author: Simon Musgrave
notes: Recorded at Tulehu and Tengah-tengah, Ambon Island.The name Sou Amana Teru means 'langauge of the three villages', and the language is centred in the communities of Tulehu, Tengah-tengah and Tial on Ambon Island. The SIL code TLU is based on the name Tulehu, often used to refer to this language.
classification: Austronesian, Malayo-Polynesian, Central-Eastern, Central Malayo-Polynesian, Central Maluku, East, Seram, Nunusaku, Piru Bay, East, Seram Straits, Ambon

author: back
glottocode: Probably a spatial relation and not a bodypart

author: he/she
glottocode: almost never used - reduced form 'i' used

author: they
glottocode: rarely used, reduced form isi/si used

author: all
glottocode: only used as bound form with pronouns e.g. amusimu = all of us
